// Particles (approximate and may need specific stress rules/context)
// Mongolian particles often attach as suffixes or clitics. Standalone particles are fewer.
юм      jʊm $u      // (declarative particle, often "is")
уу      ʊ: $u       // (interrogative particle - for yes/no questions, back vowel words)
үү      u: $u       // (interrogative particle - for yes/no questions, front vowel words)
вэ      vE $u       // (interrogative particle - for wh-questions)
нь      n;I $u      // (definite particle)
ч       tS;@ $u     // (also, even)
л       l@ $u       // (just, only)
даа     dA: $u      // (emphatic/mildly persuasive)
шүү     SU: $u      // (emphatic, "indeed", "mind you")

// Prepositions (Mongolian uses postpositions primarily, and case suffixes)
// For words that function somewhat like prepositions in English:
дээр    d'e:r      // on, above (functions as a postposition or noun)
доор    d'O:r      // under, below (postposition/noun)
хажууд  xadZ'U:d   // beside, next to (postposition/noun)
өмнө    2mn@_       // before, in front of (postposition/noun)
ард     Ard_        // behind (postposition/noun)
руу     rU: $u      // towards (directional suffix/postposition)
-аас    A:s $u      // from (ablative case suffix, many forms based on harmony)
-д      d@ $u       // to, at, in (locative/dative case suffix, many forms)

// Conjunctions
ба      ba $u       // and (mostly for joining single words or short phrases)
бөгөөд  b2g'2:d $pause // and, and also (more formal, for clauses)
буюу    bʊj'U: $pause // or (alternative)
эсвэл   Esv'El $pause // or (choice)
харин   xar;'In $pause // but, however
гэхдээ  gExd'e: $pause // but, although
тийм    t;'i:m $u    // so, thus (can be used as "yes")
учраас  ʊtSr'A:s $pause // because

// Questions (interrogative pronouns/adverbs)
